We work on challenging and exciting projects that shape the way we evolve,
adapt and transform the industries we work in. We rally together, drawing on
the diverse skills across our teams and create environments where great ideas
are heard.

This opportunity will see you join a reputable company with a highly
experienced team who work together to develop and provide solutions for our
customers.

UGL is currently looking for an experienced Senior Secondary Electrical
Engineer to become a key member of the Power Utilities teams based in Brisbane
and Sydney. You will be responsible for providing detailed designs, developing
specifications and interface with management on design issues

** About the role **

The Senior Secondary Engineer will build and maintain strong relationships
with the inhouse construction teams and our client to effectively deliver to
client expectations. This opportunity will see you join our multi-disciplined
in-house engineering team working to solve complex problems throughout the
project lifecycle across all known aspect of secondary system design
involvement. You will:

· Plan and conduct professional engineering work on relevant aspect of EHV/HV
Strategic Planning and Conceptual Design

· Provide a detail design services, consult, recommend and advise on
specialist engineering areas that would include but not be limited to:
Protection Detailed Design (Protection Logic/Setting files, etc.); Primary
Plant and Secondary System Equipment Specification and Procurement (CT, VT,
CB, TFMR, etc..); Protection/Control Detail Schematics and Integration; Grid
Metering, Power Quality and High Speed Monitoring Installations; Load flow,
Fault level and dynamic studies and analyses; Engineering Network/Data Network
Architecture and Configuration; Control System Detailed Design and
Configuration (EMS and Distribution Automation); Communication Systems
(including Data Network and Bearer Network systems design); General AC & DC
System Specification and Distribution Design; Power Generation, including
renewable energy sources detailed design involvement and system integration,
etc.

· Provide technical support to the Business Development and Tendering as
required.

· Assist with site commissioning if required (short term in general)

· When required, assume the role of Design (Package) Leader in accordance with
the Company's Engineering procedures

· Plan, coordinate and mentor other engineers

· Build and maintain relationships with key stakeholders

** About You ** ** **

· Engineering Degree

· Understanding of the power system and power utilities operational
requirements and preferably utility-based or engineering consultancy design
experience

· Strong computer skills and industry experience in a diverse range of
relevant Electrical Engineering software packages / equipment suppliers and
products.

· Proactively seek to continuously improve performance, deliverables and work
efficiencies

· Positive approach to safety

· Ability to manage multiple stakeholders

· Excellent relationship building, problem solving, commercial and negotiation
skills

